## Key findings this run

- Task 109 (network model): 26 innate immunity bridging nodes found in autoantibody PPI network; 6/18 communities have innate connections; all 9 autoantibody seed targets reachable from innate genes (mean distance 1.4 hops); community 17 has highest innate connectivity (13 bridging nodes including IL6, IL1B, MYD88, TRAF6)
- Task 110 (mimicry prediction): 36 unique human targets ranked by mimicry strength; ENO2 (tier 1/acute, mimicry=0.80) and CAMK2A (tier 2/subacute, mimicry=0.42) independently validated as both mimicry hits AND autoantibody network seeds — strong convergent evidence
- Task 107 (partial): Pre-treatment deficiency score vs IVIG transcriptional response shows no significant correlation (n=5-9), but scRNA direction consistent with hypothesis (high-deficiency mean response 0.93 vs low 0.33)

## Previous findings (tasks 104-106)

- Task 104: Lectin complement FCN1 trends higher in PANS (bulk FC=1.40)
- Task 105: ISGs elevated in PANS (OAS1 FC=1.64, ISG15 FC=1.58)
- Task 106: Composite deficiency score does NOT separate PANS from controls (p>0.3) — innate deficiency is functional/genetic, not transcriptomic

